# Audit198 gap closure, 2026-07-21 (GOVERNANCE_OWNERSHIP category --
# RULE-048 "Every software module and AI component shall have clearly
# defined ownership, responsibilities, authority, inputs, outputs,
# reporting requirements, and escalation paths."). GitHub's own CODEOWNERS
# mechanism (real PR-review-routing enforcement, not just a doc) is the
# per-module ownership half of RULE-048; ai-os/CONSTITUTION.yaml's
# reconciled_against_code_2026-07-14 list + AGENTS.md's Operating Rules
# 1-11 (PR/CI gate, agent authorization) are the escalation-path half
# (an AI agent or human contributor cannot merge without review routed
# through the owner(s) named here).
#
# Single-collaborator repo as of 2026-07-21 (confirmed via
# `gh api repos/FChecklist/compliance-tracker/collaborators`) -- every
# path below names the same owner today. Recorded per-module rather than
# as one blanket "*" line so this file is READY for the moment a second
# owner is added to a specific module (change one line, not restructure
# the whole file), and so the module boundaries this repo actually has
# are visible in one place -- itself part of what RULE-048 asks for.
#
# AI components (the "AI component" half of RULE-048): ownership of the
# AI Team roster/dispatch system itself is documented in
# src/lib/ai-team/roster.ts and ai-os/CONSTITUTION.yaml's
# orchestrator_governance section, not duplicated here -- CODEOWNERS
# governs human-reviewable code paths, not runtime AI role assignments.

# Default owner for anything not matched more specifically below.
*                                   @FChecklist

# Governance / constitution / audit -- highest-sensitivity paths, always
# routed to the repo owner.
/ai-os/CONSTITUTION.yaml           @FChecklist
/ai-os/                            @FChecklist
/AGENTS.md                         @FChecklist
/CLAUDE.md                         @FChecklist

# CI/CD + guardrail scripts -- changes here can silently weaken every
# other coverage/guardrail check, so review routing is explicit rather
# than falling through to the blanket rule by coincidence.
/.github/workflows/                @FChecklist
/scripts/                          @FChecklist

# Database schema + migrations -- irreversible-by-nature changes.
/src/lib/db/schema.ts              @FChecklist
/drizzle/                          @FChecklist

# AI platform core (policy enforcement, model routing, caching, AI team
# dispatch) -- the "AI component" surface area RULE-048 names explicitly.
/src/lib/policy-enforcement-engine.ts   @FChecklist
/src/lib/ai-team/                       @FChecklist
/src/lib/llm-response-cache.ts          @FChecklist
/src/lib/cache-governance.ts            @FChecklist
